    "updated_at": "2018-02-12T11:10:55Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "when only scalars are passed this *is* ambiguous because of ``__getitem__`` coercion, but slices are not coerced to like scalars, so it is unambiguous. To be unambiguous, a fully indexed row, column indexer (even if empty) must be passed. This is already indicated in the docs: http://pandas-docs.github.io/pandas-docs-travis/advanced.html#using-slicers."
